    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1644"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1644">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/13.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence, I have the
                    honor to enclose herewith, for your information, a copy of a memorandum by the
                    Solicitor of this Department, dated April 4, 1912, dealing with the subject of
                    our treaty right to establish wireless telegraph stations not only in the Canal
                    Zone but on the Isthmus of Panama itself, and to inquire whether it is your
                    desire that this Department now proceed to notify the Panaman Government of the
                    purpose of the Government of the United States, in accordance with the rights
                    granted by treaty, to acquire sites for wireless stations at the points
                    indicated in your communication of January 23, 1912, and to take steps to obtain
                    the necessary control of these sites.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
